{
  "texts": [
    "This configuration allows operation at both sub-synchronous and supersynchronous speeds, enabling the turbine to extract maximum energy across various wind speeds [4,5].",
    "The back-toback converter comprises two power electronic converters: the Rotor Side Converter (RSC) and Grid Side Converter (GSC).",
    "The RSC regulates the rotor currents to control electrical torque, enhancing electricity generation, while the GSC regulates rotor frequency and reactive power [6,7].The ability of these converters to control both active and reactive power makes DFIGs unique in wind power systems [8].",
    "DFIG-based systems also contribute to grid stability and voltage control, which is increasingly significant as wind energy integration progresses.",
    "However, wind energy poses challenges such as rapid fluctuations in frequency and voltage stability [9,10]."
  ]
}